ftbquests.chapter.tier_6__luv.quest25244: Most assembly line recipes require a thing called research, most people get confused by this but its kinda simple.
The data sticks that you see on recipes are made on the Scanner. Which is a pretty simple machine, you scan an item/block and that data enters the stick.

You will need to put the data stick in a data reception hatch. The most basic one supports upto 9 sticks, and you can only have 1 on the multiblock. But you will be able to upgrade it onto an advanced reception hatch soon enough.

Later on you will upgrade into Optical and CWU (Which i think is computation data) That you will make by using computers and using on a research station. But we are not gonna dive into that so much because its on ZPM.
Just FYI, the Data Orbs are only made on a research station and the data sticks can only be used in the Scanner. So dont bother with them.

ftbquests.chapter.tier__ev.quest70084053: Silicone rubber is used to cover higher tier cables, typical rubber will not last enough.

Silicone rubber is capable of covering all tiers of cables, but as an alternative you can also use styrene-butadiene rubber, which is also capable of covering all types of cables, however, it does require some petrochem stuff that you might have not done yet. I recommend you checking out the oil distillation quest too.
Also, it's &lrequired&r for LuV+ electric pumps.
ftbquests.chapter.tier__ev.quest71986629: Now you can get IV hatches.
This will be used instead of glass/tempered glass in IV-UV machines (don't ask me why UHV+ machines use regular glass).
ftbquests.chapter.tier__ev.quest73270190: Probably the most useful ME device.

By inserting encoded patterns, you can request an item to be crafted, the provider will push items from the system to a nearby inventory and wait for the encoded result to be sent into the system through itself or another ME Pattern Provider (or any other automatic way that isn't done by the player).
ftbquests.chapter.tier__ev.quest75178286: Yes, but don't worry, you still need to get tungstensteel.

ftbquests.chapter.tier__ev.quest75936491: GG!, you got to the moon, but it isn't the end, not even close.
Explore the moon to find a village full of lunarian villagers, so much fun!
In these villages you may find a hidden dungeon below them (or near by)
Instead of mining everywhere, just look for a little entrance, you will need to mine just a few blocks to enter the first stronghold-like staircase.
The Globe will be placed on world in a room, It may look scary at first glance. But remember, you are playing on peaceful mode, no mob will ever spawn!
You will need atleast 2 to get titanium, fortunately you can replicate them using the forming press.
ftbquests.chapter.tier__ev.quest80584498: You did it, you got polytetrafluoroethylene. Huge milestone!
Now get the large chemical reactor and make your setup better. You like this don't you?
Check second page to see the advantages of this over singleblock chemical reactors.
1. LCRs have perfect overclock, meaning if you overclock a recipe by a tier, instead of being 2x faster it's gonna be 4x faster!
2. You can skip some basic (and not so much) chemistry lines by using an LCR. For example, sulfuric acid can now be made using sulfur and water.
3. You can overclock an LCR like an EBF, allowing you to do next tier recipes.
4. Later on, you'll be able to put cleaning maintenance hatches on them, meaning you can do cleanroom recipes outside of one!
ftbquests.chapter.tier__ev.quest83303295: You can also get fluorine by deepslate dust processing. It's super easy and cheap, and you also get a lot of byproducts.
Rock crusher (EV) - deepslate dust - biotite dust - fluorine.
ftbquests.chapter.tier__ev.quest83496282: This quest used to call for electrolyzing water... please don't!
You have petrochem, and reacting methane gas with water yields &linsane&r amounts of hydrogen. Just make sure to keep some for further chemistry!
ftbquests.chapter.tier__ev.quest84190092: Feel free to solidify this into plates and put these into a forming press with tempered glass, it's not used for anything else.
ftbquests.chapter.tier__ev.quest84446811: Decently easy to make, and very useful
ftbquests.chapter.tier__ev.quest85216532: This is exactly why you needed petrochem, good luck with the TNT.
ftbquests.chapter.tier__ev.quest86276906: There is multiple ways to get oxygen.
ftbquests.chapter.tier__ev.quest89161775: This is an upgraded version of the typical ME Pattern Provider.
You cannot get the non-extended version of this, so I wouldn't recommend using this as the normal provider, but it has it's use cases.
The advanced pattern provider has the ability to use advanced patterns - that means selecting where the provider is gonna push every item from the pattern.
So, for example, you could make coal enter behind the furnace and iron through the top.
To do this, however, you will need a custom advanced pattern encoder.
ftbquests.chapter.tier__ev.quest90075844: This is the first custom multiblock in the pack.
The moon miner is sort of a "big" multiblock, that will be your only way to make titanium for now.
It needs a lot of stainless steel casings, so if you haven't passived or atleast made more than like 5 EBFs at this point, you really should do it.
ftbquests.chapter.tier__ev.quest97203328: This is the distillation tower, a cool funny multiblock to distill your oil at semi max efficiency.
Would 100%% recommend it, in case you want to use things like diesel for power gen or combustion generators, as well as a better ethylene route.

ftbquests.chapter.tips_and_tricks.quest6: Compressed hammers are a way to make gravel, sand and dust more efficiently by hammering down the compressed versions of the blocks.

ftbquests.chapter.tips_and_tricks.quest8: Welcome to Gregtech, pipes dont work like other mods, and you will need a conveyor/pump if u want to extract something without an auto output machine.
To make it work without auto output you will need a Screwdriver to configure the covers.
The energy conduits adapt through the block they're connected to.
So if a solar panel transfers 16k/t  they gonna transfer 16k/t too.
